<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05510</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REGULATING THE MANUFACTURE, USE, SALE, PACKAGING, DISTRIBUTION AND ADVERTISEMENTS OF VAPOR PRODUCTS AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Refers "Vapor Products" as battery-powered devices that heat a solution, blend or gel, which may or may not contain nicotine, to a temperature that allows the production of vapor, also termed as Electronic Nicotine or Electronic Non-Nicotine Delivery Systems ( E N D S / E N N D S ).

Aims to mitigate and monitor the risks of Vapor Products by imposing strict product standards and comprehensive restrictions on their sales and consumption through: creation of an Inter-Agency Committee; protection of minors; ban on flavorings, except for tobacco and menthol; maintenance of post - market records on adverse health events; prohibition against use in certain public
places; severe penalties for non - compliance, among others.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>HERRERA-DY, BERNADETTE &quot;BH&quot;</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-11-18</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRADE AND INDUSTRY ON 2019-11-20</td></tr></table>